diff:1251799407:1251799407:=1,18d0%0a%3c ! Running Dspam and Tmda together%0a%3c Ok this is not documented anywhere so I will document this here:%0a%3c %0a%3c If you run Dspam an Tmda you will only want the Mail in your Tmda, that has not been caught by Dspam. For that you will have to configure Dspam per User via the .qmail-file:%0a%3c %0a%3c What Tmda does is link the two users:%0a%3c %0a%3c  .qmail-testuser-default -> /var/vpopmail/domains/domain.ch/.qmail-testuser%0a%3c %0a%3c in this case the .qmail-default file contains:%0a%3c %0a%3c  | /var/vpopmail/bin/vdelivermail '' postmaster@domain.ch%0a%3c  %0a%3c and the .qmail-testuser-default cotains%0a%3c %0a%3c  | /usr/bin/dspam --deliver=innocent --user testuser@domain.ch --stdout%0a%3c  |preline -f /home/ywesee/src/tmda/tmda-1.1.12/bin/tmda-filter -c /var/vpopmail/domains/domain.ch/testuser/.tmda/config -t /var/vpopmail/domains/rigiwin.ch/bsiegfried/.tmda/templates/%0a%3c  |/var/vpopmail//bin/vdelivermail '' /var/vpopmail/domains/domain.ch/testuser%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
